<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 20 at 3:38PM CST  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT NORTHERN MCCURTAIN COUNTY THROUGH
415 PM CST...
At 337 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 16 miles east of Cloudy, or 30 miles southeast of
Clayton, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Plunketville, Smithville, Watson, Bethel, Battiest, Pickens, Mount
Herman, and Sherwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
